name: ExtensionImmunization_Reaction
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.Immunization.reaction` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `Immunization.reaction` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `Immunization.reaction` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`Immunization.reaction` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `Immunization.reaction` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `Immunization.reaction` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `Immunization.reaction` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `Immunization.reaction` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `Immunization.reaction`, but has no comparisons.

element.short: Details of a reaction that follows immunization
element.definition: Categorical data indicating that an adverse event is associated in time to an immunization.
element.comment: A reaction may be an indication of an allergy or intolerance and, if this is determined to be the case, it should be recorded as a new AllergyIntolerance resource instance as most systems will not query against past Immunization.reaction elements.
